Text: FW TxWAG Rescue DogsIf you know anyone lookingthe first sounds urgent Sarah Hlavinka McConnell Associate General Counsel Compaq Computer Corporation MS SH Houston TX Phone Facsimile mailto Original Message From Cindy mailto Sent Wednesday October PM To Subject TxWAG Rescue Dogs Hi all I currently have two rescues Im looking for homes for The most urgent situation is a dog in Dallas Riley He is years Must be the only pet and go to a home without children The ideal situation would be an older settled couple or person Riley was abused and is a terrified dog He needs to have a home with a yard because as of now he cant go for a walk He shuts down if he sees another dog a person a car anything unfamiliar Im sure the right person could build his confidence back but for now he needs a very secure environment I need to find Riley a home by this Sunday And he cant be shipped I do have a picture of him My other rescue is Jessie I still havent found a home for her But she is not so urgent Jessie also needs to be the only pet she terrorized the other two dogs she used to live with Its possible she was abused she doesnt trust anyone and will growl at you She needs to go to a home without children I cant take a chance with her actually being pushed to the point of biting She is getting along fine with Jazz and Shasta but I keep thinking she is going to start feeling comfortable one of these days and our smooth times will be over Jessie will need someone with lots of patience and who has time to work with her She needs rules and someone to enforce them She is a pretty dominant little gal If anyone has any suggestions call me or email me Thanks Cindy Yahoo Groups Sponsor Get your FREE credit report with a FREE CreditCheck Monitoring Service trial GitnDbQCAAySSFAArHolBTM To unsubscribe from this group send an email to Your use of Yahoo Groups is subject to infoterms

Subject FW UNDERSTANDING WHAT HAPPENED AT ENRON Be sure and read it all Feudalism You have two cows Your lord takes some of the milk Fascism You have two cows The government takes both hires you to take care of them and sells you the milk Pure Communism You have two cows Your neighbors help take care of them and you all share the milk Applied Communism You have two cows You must take care of them but the government takes all the milk Totalitarianism You have two cows The government takes them both and denies they ever existed Milk is banned Pure Democracy You have two cows You and your neighbors decide who gets the milk Representative Democracy You have two cows Your neighbors pick someone to tell you who gets the milk Mexican Democracy You have two cows The government takes both and drafts you into the army European Democracy You have two cows The EU commission decides which regulations for feeding and milking apply If there arent any they invent some They pay you not to milk the cows They take both cows shoot one milk the other and pour the milk down the drain They then require you to fill out forms accounting for the missing cows American Democracy The government promises to give you two cows if you vote for it After the election the president is impeached for speculating in cow futures The press dubs the affair cowgate but supports the president The cows sue you for breach of contract Your legal bills exceed your annual income You settle out of court and declare bankruptcy Capitalism You have two cows You sell one and buy a bull Your herd multiplies and the economy grows You sell them and retire on the income Enron Venture Capitalism You have two cows You sell three of them to your publicly listed company using letters of credit opened by your brotherinlaw at the bank then execute a debtequity swap with an associated general offer so that you get all four cows back with a tax exemption for five cows The milk rights of the six cows are transferred via an intermediary to a Cayman Island company secretly owned by the majority shareholder who sells the rights to all seven cows back to your listed company The annual report says the company owns eight cows with an option on one more Get your FREE download of MSN Explorer at intlasp

FW TxWAG WTCARES AwardTake a look at Jessie She is unbelievably cute Note that Cindy says that Ive had Jessie over a month now she wagged her tail for the first time last week Poor little Jessie Sarah Hlavinka McConnell Associate General Counsel Compaq Computer Corporation MS SH Houston TX Phone Facsimile mailto Original Message From Cindy mailto Sent Tuesday October PM To Subject TxWAG WTCARES Award Hi Everyone I just returned from Montgomery While there I attended the WTCA dinnermeeting TX WAG was awarded a very nice plaque in appreciation from WTCARES You can read a little blurb about it on the web site While you are there take a look at Jessie She is a yo female I am fostering right now Im looking for someone with terrier experience for Jessie No kids no other pets Ive had Jessie over a month now she wagged her tail for the first time last week If any of yall know someone that might be interested ask them to contact me And about the plaque dont yall think Jeff and Gigi should have the plaque Since its always their digs where we WAG Cindy Yahoo Groups Sponsor FREE COLLEGE MONEY CLICK HERE to search scholarships PvpGDmCAAySSFAArHolBTM To unsubscribe from this group send an email to Your use of Yahoo Groups is subject to infoterms

RE Land Cash Flow Analysis Cc Michael We calculated but at acre Terry seems to think there is no way we can get if for less than that and I voiced my opinion not to go higher He said that they did mention owner financing late last week as low as so maybe we could go higher on the per acre price We didnt calculate hunting income or taxes assuming roughly they would cancel out Also Terry indicates that the farm really wants half not sure if he needs to tie out with Daddy so that would leave us with responsibility for each I think the cropland base numbers are too high on your spread sheet If you add the rice base grain base and cropland base you come up in excess of the total acreage I can redo the sheet this afternoon The end result we had is that we would each be out of pocket approximately month Mark and I are willing to do that Not sure what you are thinking there Sarah Original Message From Michael Hlavinka mailto Sent Monday November AM To McConnell Sarah Subject Land Cash Flow Analysis Sarah Ive done some cash flow calculations on that land using the numbers given to us by Daddy assuming ac and financing Do they agree with what you and Mark have come up with Have I left something out My calculations indicate that if you can purchase for ac and finance at you break even with ac rental on the rice base I dont know if that is possible You can change the numbers in the worksheet and the calculations should update to reflect the correct values Let me know what you think Michael

FW TxWAG earthdog practicetesti guess we wont make it Sarah Hlavinka McConnell Associate General Counsel Compaq Computer Corporation MS SH Houston TX Phone Facsimile mailto Original Message From Cindy mailto Sent Saturday October PM To Subject TxWAG earthdog practicetest If anyone would like to practice Earthdoggin Tejas Earthdog Club is having their digin next Saturday in Brookshire If you would like to come out at am and help dig in the tunnels you can practice for free If you would just like to come out and practice come out between npm the cost is per dog to practice as much as you want The actual test is the following weekend Directions are from Houston west on I to Peachridge Rd Exit and turn South left onto Peachridge Rd go approximately mile to Donigan Rd a stop sign here Make a right Proceed miles Donigan Rd Entrance will be on the right Cindy Yahoo Groups Sponsor FREE COLLEGE MONEY CLICK HERE to search scholarships PvpGDmCAAySSFAArHolBTM To unsubscribe from this group send an email to Your use of Yahoo Groups is subject to infoterms
